Package: turborec
Version: 2.1.0
Section: sound
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Cristian Cezar Moises <ethicalhacker@riseup.net>
Depends: ffmpeg, python3 (>= 3.8), python3-tk
Homepage: https://github.com/cristiancmoises/turborec
Description: State-of-the-art hardware-accelerated screen and audio recorder
 Turbo Recorder captures your screen and audio at the best quality your
 hardware can deliver. It probes the machine and configures everything
 automatically: operating system, display server, CPU vendor, GPU, the best
 available hardware video encoder, the screen resolution, and the microphone
 and system-audio sources. It then builds a quality-first FFmpeg pipeline and
 records.
 .
 Two front-ends share one engine: a cross-platform Python CLI and GUI
 (turborec) and a fast, dependency-light Bash CLI for Linux/X11
 (turborecorder).
